http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/BSNL-employees-seek-better-facilities/article14011160.ece

A large number of contract workers at the Bharat Sanchar Nigam Ltd. (BSNL) staged a protest here on Wednesday demanding regularisation of their services and hike in salary.Protesting under the banner of Karnataka State BSNL Non-Permanent Workers’ Union, affiliated to the Centre of Indian Trade Unions (CITU), they staged a dharna outside the Deputy Commissioner’s office here. The protesters urged the Union government to regularise their services, increase their salary by a minimum of Rs. 18,000 a month and other facilities.